t the very philosophers from whom he drew influence. Feke reveals how Ptolemy's unique system is at once a critique of prevailing philosophical trends and a conception of the world in which mathematics reigns supreme.A compelling work of scholarship, Ptolemy's Philosophy demonstrates how Ptolemy situated mathematics at the very foundation of all philosophy-theoretical and practical-and advanced the mathematical way of life as the true path to human perfection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aAlexandrian school. 0aNeoplatonism. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aAlmagest 1.1.  aAmmonius Saccas.  aAntiochus of Ascalon.  aAristotelian philosophy.  aAristotle.  aClaudius Ptolemy.  aHarmonics.  aNeoplatonism.  aOn the Kritêrion.  aPlanetary Hypotheses.  aPlatonic philosophy.  aTetrabiblos.  aastrology.  aastronomy.  acosmology.  aelement theory.  aempiricism.  aepistemology.  aethics.  aharmonia.  aharmonic ratios.  aharmonics.  aheavens.  ahuman soul.  amathematics.  ametaphysics.  amiddle Platonism.  apractical philosophy.  apsychological theory.  ascientific method.  asoul.  atheoretical philosophy.  avirtues.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060420708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2018z9783110603200oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060659140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691184036zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de